Akenerji 2nd-Quarter Loss 40 Million Liras, Misses Estimate

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-08-25T15:08:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/akenerji-2nd-quarter-loss-40-million-liras-misses-estimate-1-.html
Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR) , a
Turkish utility, said losses in the second quarter widened,
exceeding estimates.  The loss increased to 39.9 million liras from 22.2 million
liras in the same period of 2010, Akenerji said in a statement
to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  today. The company was expected
to report a loss of 16.1 million liras, according to the average
of nine analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Sales gained to 137.9 million liras from 84.8 million liras
in the second quarter of last year. Financial expenses surged to
72.2 million liras from 17.4 million liras, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Bentley in Istanbul at 
